content:
Using the Action toolbar, you can launch a single OmniScript from a variety of contexts without configuring a Visualforce page for each context. For example, you can launch an OmniScript from a Contact, Account, Case record, or Customer Community, using a single Visualforce page.

Beginning with Winter '18, the Action Toolbar is no longer available.

You can apply filters so that the OmniScript is available only if certain conditions are met. To launch Vlocity OmniScripts, enter an Apex page, or a URL with parameters as the Target URL. 

LWC components, such as LWC OmniScripts, cannot be accessed directly from a URL and must embedded on a page.

Create a Visualforce Page to Display the Action Toolbar

This lists and displays images of Action Toolbar style types.
title: Launching OmniScript from Action Toolbar
